Start with an ending. Doesn't have to be specific. Something as simple as reach X destination or the end of a first date. Then figure out where you want to start your story. Afterwards, everything you write will be about getting from Start to End. Every part of your story should move you closer to the end. You can go fast or slow, it's your call, as long as you keep writing towards that ending.
And when you reach that ending, you're free to close off the story... or think of a new ending to work towards.

Example
> Ending: end of the first date
> Starting point 1: how anon got that date, or
> Starting point 2: anon is already on the date
> Choose starting point 2
> Story is about Anon getting to know Waifur
> Date starts strong but let's say ends horribly
> You can now decide how if the story ends here
> Ending 1 (close-off): Anon and Waifur part ways
> Ending 2 (continue): Anon admits the date ended horribly but convinces Waifur to go on a second date to make up for
it
> Ending 3 (close-off): date ended horribly but Waifur had fun and wants to continue the date over at her apartment (cue sexytime epilogue)
